OL,3,CMinister says he won't play a part in
OL,4,Cstopping GP practises from going
OL,5,Cprivate
OL,7,FArmagh GP, Dr. Conor Moore said: "If
OL,8,Fthe department doesn't engage and we
OL,9,Fdon't see improvement, we're going to
OL,10,Fhave to consider all options in order
OL,11,Fto to keep the ourselves going.
OL,13,F"And I think at a point in time where
OL,14,Fpractices' finances are so constrained
OL,15,Fby the contractual arrangements,
OL,16,Fthey'll have to make a decision at a
OL,17,Fpoint in time that it's no longer
OL,18,Fprofitable and and decide on what
OL,19,Ftheir next steps are."
