OL,3,CMinister says he won't play a part in
OL,4,Cstopping GP practises from going
OL,5,Cprivate
OL,7,FDr. Frances O'Hagan from British
OL,8,FMedical Association said: "I
OL,9,Fpersonally don't provide a private
OL,10,Fservice here in Northern Ireland for
OL,11,Fthat reason.
OL,13,F"That's my personal opinion. But there
OL,14,Fare other people who are comfortable
OL,15,Fto ask people to pay. And to be
OL,16,Fhonest, there are patients who are
OL,17,Ftaking that option, and they are going
OL,18,Fto see a private GP now and paying for
OL,19,Fit."
